  "text": "Shin et al. [CITATION_1] studied computationally the comparison between four turbofan engines in the ground vortex effect. They studied the full-scale geometry. These four engines are: CF6-80a, Trent-700, Trent-900, and GE-Nx-1b64. They found that there are two main types of vortices around intake which are: an inlet vortex, and a trailing vortex, Figure 11 .",
